        <briefdescription>
<para>Functions in <ref refid="xaxipmon__selftest_8c" kindref="compound">xaxipmon_selftest.c</ref>. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Run a self-test on the driver/device.</para><para>The test<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Resets the device,</para></listitem><listitem><para>Writes a value into the Range Registers of Incrementer 0 and reads it back for comparison.</para></listitem><listitem><para>Resets the device again.</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_axi_pmon" kindref="compound">XAxiPmon</ref> instance.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS if the value read from the Range Register of Incrementer 0 is the same as the value written.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE Otherwise</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>This is a destructive test in that resets of the device are performed. Refer to the device specification for the device status after the reset operation. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
